{#- The single GENERATED region of README.md (mode = Merge): the version /
    toolchain / pre-commit-gate-count paragraph, projected from repo-facts.
    One marker set per file — see the merge module's doc comment in
    crates/ggen-engine/src/generation_rules.rs. -#}
{%- set vrows = sparql(query='PREFIX rf: <http://ggen.org/repo-facts#> SELECT ?wv ?tc WHERE { rf:doc rf:workspaceVersion ?wv ; rf:toolchainChannel ?tc . } ORDER BY ?wv') -%}
{%- set v = sparql_first(rows=vrows) -%}
{%- set grows = sparql(query='PREFIX rf: <http://ggen.org/repo-facts#> SELECT ?o ?name WHERE { ?g a rf:Gate ; rf:order ?o ; rf:name ?name . } ORDER BY ?o') -%}
{%- set gnames = sparql_values(rows=grows, column="name") -%}
Current version: `{{ v.wv }}` (workspace version in `Cargo.toml`; nightly Rust toolchain
`{{ v.tc }}`, pinned via `rust-toolchain.toml`). The Definition of Done is `just
pre-commit`, which chains {{ grows | length }} gates: {{ gnames | join(sep=" → ") }}. This project is
under active, fast-moving development — see [Maturity & Known Limitations](#maturity--known-limitations)
before depending on it for anything production-critical.
